# Gera lotes para prever os prximos n_teste valores com base nos uv valores anteriores (multiplo)
def multi_output(df, uv, nt):
    df = df.to_numpy()
    Tx = uv
    Ty = nt
    X = []
    Y = []
    for t in range(len(df) - Tx - Ty + 1):
        x = df[t:t+Tx]
        X.append(x)
        y = df[t+Tx:t+Tx+Ty]
        Y.append(y)

    X = np.array(X).reshape(-1, Tx, 1) # Rede Neural Recorrente e LSTM
    Y = np.array(Y).reshape(-1, Ty)

    Xtrain, Ytrain = X[:-1], Y[:-1]
    Xtest, Ytest = X[-1:], Y[-1:]
    
    return Xtrain, Ytrain, Xtest, Ytest



# Transformao logartmica
def get_log(df, reverse=False):
    if not reverse:
        df_log = np.log(df)
        df_log = df_log.replace([np.inf, -np.inf], np.nan)
        df_log = df_log.fillna(0)
        df_log.columns = ['Logaritmo']
        return df_log
    else:
        df_rev = np.exp(df)
        return df_rev


# Transformao de diferena
def get_diff(df, reverse=False, fv=0):
    if not reverse:
        df_diff = df.diff()
        df_diff = df_diff.replace([np.inf, -np.inf], np.nan)
        df_diff = df_diff.fillna(0)
        # Salva primeiro valor para reverter a diferena
        first_value = df.iloc[0]
        df_diff.columns = ['Diferenciao']
        return df_diff, first_value
    else:
        df_rev = df.cumsum() + fv
        return df_rev


# Mtricas para Anlise Exploratria
def get_status(df):
    print('\n\n\n', df.describe())
    # seasonal_decompose
    result = seasonal_decompose(df, model='additive')
    result.plot();

    fig, axes = plt.subplots(1, 3)
    axes[0].hist(df)
    axes[0].set_title('Histogram')
    axes[1].boxplot(df, )
    axes[1].set_title('Boxplot')
    plot_acf(df, ax=axes[2])
    plt.show();

    # shapiro-wilk
    stat, p = shapiro(df)
    print('Sapiro: Statistics=%.4f, p=%.4f' % (stat, p));

    # Kpss
    result = kpss(df)

    # Acessar os resultados
    kpss_statistic = result[0].round(3)
    p_value = result[1].round(3)
    lags_used = result[2]
    critical_values = result[3]

    print(f"KPSS Statistic: {kpss_statistic}")
    print(f"P-Value: {p_value}")
    print(f"Lags Used: {lags_used}")
    print(f"Critical Values: {critical_values}")


# Grfico de linhas
def get_line(df):
    fig = px.line(df, x=df.index, y=df.columns, labels={'variable': 'Varivel'})
    fig.update_xaxes(title='Perodo')
    fig.update_yaxes(title='Valor')
    fig.show()


# Mtricas de Avaliao de Modelos
def get_metricas(real, predito):
    mse = mean_squared_error(real, predito).round(3)
    rmse = np.sqrt(mse).round(3)
    mae = mean_absolute_error(real, predito).round(3)
    mape = mean_absolute_percentage_error(real, predito).round(3)
    return {'mse': mse, 'rmse': rmse, 'mae': mae, 'mape': mape}

n_teste = 12  # Nmero de testes
uv = 24  # ltimos valores/registros
epochs = 100
activation = 'tanh'
neurons = 64 # Antes 24
index_treino = df.index.isin(df.iloc[:-n_teste,:].index)
index_teste = ~index_treino

# Lotes
model_data = df['y'].copy()

# Prever os prximos n_teste valores com base nos uv valores anteriores (previso direta)
Xtrain_m, Ytrain_m, Xtest_m, Ytest_m = multi_output(model_data, uv, n_teste)

treino = model_data[index_treino]
teste = model_data[index_teste]
In [ ]:
i = Input(shape=(uv,1))
x = LSTM(neurons, activation=activation)(i)
# x = LSTM(neurons, return_sequences=True, activation=activation)(i)
# x = GlobalMaxPooling1D()(x)
x = Dense(n_teste)(x)
model = Model(i, x)

model.compile(loss='mse', optimizer='adam')

r = model.fit(
    Xtrain_m, Ytrain_m,
    epochs=epochs,
    validation_data=(Xtest_m, Ytest_m), verbose=0)

results = pd.DataFrame(model.predict(Xtest_m)[0], index=teste.index)

full = model_data.copy()
full[index_teste] = results.iloc[:,0] # Popula original
df['y_pred'] = full

get_metricas(df['y_pred'][index_teste], df.iloc[index_teste,0])
